      "description": "<p>The SimpleLink&trade; CC1312PSIP device is a System-in-Package (SiP) Sub-1 GHz wireless module supporting the 861 MHz to 1030 MHz frequency range. CC1312PSIP is supporting IEEE 802.15.4, IPv6-enabled smart objects (6LoWPAN) WiSUN, mioty and proprietary systems including the TI 15.4-Stack. The main microcontroller (MCU) in CC1312PSIP is based on an Arm&reg; Cortex&reg;-M4F main processor and optimized for low-power wireless communication, in addition the device includes an ultra low power sensor controller for advanced sensing in grid infrastructure, building automation, retail automation and medical applications. The CC1312PSIP has a software defined radio powered by an Arm&reg; Cortex&reg;-M0 and dedicated programable DSPs - this allows support for multiple physical layers and RF standards now and for the future. The built-in PA has very good efficiency and supports +14 dBm TX at 25 mA and +19 dBm TX at 69 mA.</p>",
