      "description": "<p>The SimpleLink&trade; CC2340R53-Q1 device is an AEC-Q100 Grade 2 compliant, 2.4&nbsp;GHz wireless microcontroller (MCU) targeting <a href='https://www.ti.com/wireless-connectivity/simplelink-solutions/bluetooth-low-energy/overview/overview.html'><i>Bluetooth&reg;</i> Low Energy</a> and Proprietary 2.4&nbsp;GHz applications. The device is optimized for low-power wireless communication in applications such as car access, including passive entry passive start (PEPS), phone as a key (PaaK), remote keyless entry (RKE), and tire pressure monitoring systems (TPMS). The highlighted features of this device include:</p><ul><li>Support for<i>Bluetooth&reg;</i>&nbsp; features: High Speed Mode (2&nbsp;Mbps PHY), Long Range (LE Coded 125&nbsp;kbps and 500&nbsp;kbps PHYs), and Channel Selection Algorithm #2, as well as backwards compatibility and support for key features from earlier <i>Bluetooth&reg;</i>&nbsp; Low Energy specifications.</li> <li>Bluetooth&reg Channel Sounding technology support and Algorithm Processing Unit (APU) to enable high accuracy, low cost, and secure phase-based ranging for distance estimation.<li> <li>Arm&reg Custom Data Extension (CDE) instruction support for machine learning acceleration.<li> <li>Fully-qualified <i>Bluetooth&reg;</i>&nbsp; software protocol stack included with the <a href='https://www.ti.com/tool/SIMPLELINK-LOWPOWER-F3-SDK'>SimpleLink&trade; Low Power F3 Software Development Kit (SDK)</a>.</li> <li> Advanced security features including an isolated Hardware Security Module (HSM), Secure boot and firmware updates with the root of trust from immutable system ROM, TrustZone-M based execution environment support, Secure key storage, and more.<li> <li>Ultra-low standby current less than 0.9&nbsp;&micro;A with RTC operational and full RAM retention that enables significant battery life extension especially for applications with longer sleep intervals.</li> <li>Very low average radio currents for duty-cycled BLE use-cases. Average radio current approximately 6&nbsp;&micro;A when operating in a <i>Bluetooth&reg;</i> Low Energy connection with TX output power = 0&nbsp;dBm and 1&nbsp;second connection interval.</li> <li>Integrated balun for reduced Bill-of-Material (BOM) board layout</li> <li>Excellent radio sensitivity and robustness (selectivity and blocking) performance for<i>Bluetooth&reg;</i> Low Energy (-101&nbsp;dBm for 125&nbsp;kbps LE Coded PHY, with integrated balun).</li> </ul> <p>The CC2340R53-Q1 device is part of the SimpleLink&trade; MCU platform, which consists of Wi-Fi&reg;, <i>Bluetooth&reg;</i> Low Energy, Thread&reg;, Zigbee&reg;, Sub-1 GHz MCUs, and host MCUs that all share a common, easy-to-use development environment with a single core software development kit (SDK) and rich tool set. A one-time integration of the SimpleLink&trade; platform enables you to add any combination of the portfolio's devices into your design, allowing 100 percent code reuse when your design requirements change. For more information, visit <a href='https://www.ti.com/wireless-connectivity/simplelink-solutions/overview/overview.html'>SimpleLink&trade; MCU platform</a>.</p>",
